title: Pranab Mukherjee meets Jordan's King Abdullah
text:
KV Prasad in Amman (Jordan) October 10
President Pranab Mukherjee arrived in Jordan on Saturday, becoming the first Indian Head of State to visit the west Asian country in sixty-five years. Mukherjee was given a guard of honour at the Al Husseinieh Palace and was received by King Abdullah. Both President and the King later had a closed-door meeting, which was followed by delegation-level talks. The King later hosted a lunch in honour of the President. Earlier in the day, Mukherjee inaugurated a JIFFCO plan, a joint venture between Jordan Phosphate Mines Company and IFFCO through remote. The US $ 860 million project set up in Eshidiya is already in operation. Mukherjee is on a three-nation tour that will also take him to Palestine and Israel over the next six days.
